              <a:t>Step 1: build the system prompt by assembling base prompt, skill injections from SkillRuntime, memory context from MemoryContextBuilder (max 2000 chars), and tool descriptions. Step 2: run the tool loop. We use LangGraph's create_react_agent() when providers support tool binding (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.). For others, we fall back to plan_execute: ask the LLM to generate a numbered plan, then execute each step explicitly. Step 3: detect truncation. If finish_reason='length' or 'max_tokens', the output was cut off — we enter recovery mode. Step 4: finalize. _finalize_messages() is the recovery engine with a cascade of strategies to ensure we never return an empty answer.</a:t>
